## Threat model (STRIDE summary)

| Category | Surface | Defense in this project |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Spoofing | Login, password reset, session | django-allauth, Argon2 hashing, CSRF, MFA TOTP |
| Tampering | HTTP requests, cookies | HTTPS-only cookies (prod), HSTS 1y + preload, SameSite=Lax |
| Repudiation | Auth events, admin actions | Logged via {{ "structlog" if bakery.use_observability else "django logging" }}{% if bakery.use_sentry %}; Sentry breadcrumbs{% endif %} |
| Information disclosure | Errors, debug pages, static files | `DEBUG=False` in prod; allowlist-only `ALLOWED_HOSTS`; CSP; no PII in logs |
| Denial of service | Auth endpoints, public API | `django-ratelimit`{% if bakery.api_layer == 'drf' %}; DRF throttle classes{% endif %}; gunicorn timeouts |
| Elevation of privilege | Admin, IDOR | Object-level perm checks (write these in views/viewsets); `is_staff`-gated admin |

## OWASP A01–A10 baseline (2025)

| # | Category | Defense |
| - | --- | --- |
| A01 | Broken access control | Login-required mixins, object perms in views{% if bakery.api_layer == 'drf' %}, DRF permission classes{% endif %} |
| A02 | Crypto failures | Argon2 password hash, secrets via env (never in code), HSTS, secure cookies |
| A03 | Injection | ORM-only DB access (parameterized), Jinja `{{ '{{ }}' }}` autoescape, no shell exec without `shlex` |
| A04 | Insecure design | Specs + threat model first; default-deny CORS; minimum length 12 for passwords |
| A05 | Security misconfig | Strict-mode CSP, `SECURE_*` headers, `manage.py check --deploy` in CI |
| A06 | Vulnerable components | `pip-audit` in CI, Trivy on container images, Renovate suggested |
| A07 | Auth failures | allauth rate limits (`5/5m`), MFA TOTP, email verification mandatory |
| A08 | Software/data integrity | gitleaks pre-commit + CI; signed releases recommended |
| A09 | Logging failures | Structured logs{% if bakery.use_observability %} via structlog{% endif %}{% if bakery.use_sentry %} + Sentry{% endif %}; auth events tagged |
| A10 | SSRF | Outbound HTTP via library wrappers; never accept raw URLs without allowlists |

## ASVS L2 — items you still own

These are project-specific and **not** auto-enforced by the scaffolding. Audit each release:

- [ ] Every user-input boundary has length + format validation
- [ ] Every model has object-level permission checks at view-time
- [ ] Every external API call has a timeout
- [ ] Every secret rotation procedure is documented
- [ ] Every admin user has MFA enabled

